  "text": "Compared with SNPs, the contribution of CNVs to genetic variability and breast and/or ovarian cancer risk is relatively unknown. This is the first genome-wide CNV association study of BRCA1 pathogenic variant carriers to identify CNVs that are associated with breast and/ or ovarian cancer risk, and the first implementation of the retrospective likelihood to CNV data. Our study used multiple CNV calling Figure 1 Genomic landscape at the region containing the CNV deletion overlapping CYP2A7. The location of the CNV deletion and the enhancer predicted by Hnisz et al [CITATION_1] ",
